  "prompt": "What is the opposite of the color gray?",
  "response": "The opposite of gray can vary depending on the context, such as whether you\u2019re considering color theory or aesthetic preferences. In color theory, particularly when using the traditional color wheel, gray doesn't have a direct opposite since it is a neutral color. However, you can consider vibrant colors, such as bright yellow or bright blue, as opposites in a more abstract sense, as they provide contrast against the neutrality of gray. In artistic terms, complementary or contrasting colors can also be seen as opposites.",
